<POSTDATE> 2007-09-05T16:02:00 </POSTDATE>
Has anyone mentioned the obvious?  Commodore power supplies themselves
were notorious for failing.   I've seen several that they electrloytic
caps have gone bad after all these years.  I had a 1581 power supply
that actually output 5V and 12V just fine under no load.  But once
plugged into the 1581, I re-measured and got 2.9V and 10V.   I
replaced the caps inside the power supply and it worked again.

Also, some other troubleshooting steps.  Can you boot to C64 mode
reliably, by holding down the commodore key when powering on?  If it
is a C128D, be carefull of printer adapters that connect to the
cassette port for power.  many were not designed for the metal case
and will short circuit on a 128D.

Does the problem go away when other peripherals (such as the disk
drive) are removed?
