Marco,
Two other things come to mind... you said you reseated all the socketed
chips, but did you remove, then reinsert all of them? One may have a bent pin
that is barely making contact. If any of the sockets were not from the factory,
the board traces or that socket may be bad. One other problem I had once was
distorted pins in the cartridge port. Two pins were touching intermittantly, and
flexing the main board made it work... sometimes. Examine that area carefully
under strong light to see if there is any debris (metal) or bent contacts that
may be shorting together. Other than loose solder connections at the power
connector and other ports, I've seen very few actual problems with solder on
Commodore computer boards. They were built very well. Monitors... that's a
different story. :-P

Ray
