<POSTDATE> 2007-09-07T21:39:00 </POSTDATE>
Thank you again to everyone who offered advise.  I found the problem... bad
solder joint on a pin on U11 (PLA).

The way I found the problem is that I noticed that gentle taps on the PCB
after a good boot would crash the computer.  It was most sensitive around
the bottom middle of the board.  It took about 3 hours of resoldering many
chips (trying each time in between) until I finally stumbled on the
culprit.  It's like night and day.  Previously after a good boot the board
could be crashed by slight movements/jars.  Now I can (gently) felx the PCB
and drop it.  Also (more importantly) it boots everytime now.

I guess I found that one board with the most unlikely of failures.  Now to
figure out what to do with the computer.  My wife is already telling me to
get rid of it.  She won't win this time.  Thanks again.

Marco
